## aliases

The `/aliases` node defines aliases for device tree nodes. A devicetree may have an aliases node (`/aliases`) that defines one or more alias properties. The aliases node shall be at the root of the devicetree and have the node name `/aliases`.

Each property of the `/aliases` node defines an alias. The property name specifies the alias name. The property value specifies the full path to a node in the devicetree. Alias names shall be lowercase text strings of 1 to 31 characters consisting of digits (0-9), lowercase letters (a-z), and dashes (-).

A client program may use an alias property name to refer to a full device path.

```dts
/* arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/sm8550-qrd.dts */
aliases {
    serial0 = &uart7;
    serial1 = &uart14;
};

/* DTS spec example */
aliases {
    serial0 = "/simple-bus@fe000000/serial@llc500";
    ethernet0 = "/simple-bus@fe000000/ethernet@31c000";
};
```
